            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Once the<strong> </strong>onion<strong> </strong>has softened, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and most of the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (save some for garnish!) to the pan with the<strong> curry powder</strong> and<strong> ground turmeric</strong></p><p>Increase the heat to medium and cook for 3 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/936.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/936.-step-4-x400.jpg",
